snippet: The House vote and another scheduled for Tuesday in the Senate are chiefly intended to be a political maneuver by Republican and Democratic leaders in the battle for a Louisiana Senate seat.
abstract: House votes 252 to 161 to approve bill that will direct federal government to move forward on Keystone XL oil pipeline, ahead of vote scheduled in Senate that could send measure to Pres Obama's desk; votes are chiefly intended to be political maneuvers by party leaders in drawn-out battle for Louisiana Senate seat between Democratic Sen Mary L Landrieu and Republican Rep Bill Cassidy.
lead_paragraph: The House vote and another scheduled for Tuesday in the Senate are chiefly intended to be a political maneuver by Republican and Democratic leaders in the battle for a Louisiana Senate seat.

headline.main: House Passes Bill Directing Obama to Proceed on Oil Pipeline
headline.print_headline: House Passes Bill Directing Obama to Proceed on Oil Pipeline
